      <div class="row">
        <h2 class="centered">PotaVida's Solution is Different:</h2>
        <hr>
        <br>
        <div class="col-lg-offset-2 col-lg-8">
          <p>The sun does all the work: measures sunlight (UV) exposure and shows the user when the water is disinfected<br>
          It's self-contained, reusable, and easy:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Put filled bag in the sun </li>
              <li>Press start button</li>
              <li>Red light = in progress</li> 
              <li>Green light = safe to drink</li>
            </ol>
          <p>
          Water can be purified in 3-6 hours per batch in full sunlight.<br>
          The bag can be used for transport and storage
          <br>
          There's nothing to replace or refill, with a 5-year working life and 10-year shelf life
          <br>
          At volume, it costs less than $20/unit for 5-10L capacity
          <br>
          The sensor also records usage history for download by field staff
        </p>
        </div><!-- col-lg -->
      </div><!-- row -->
      

