        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <%= image_tag('charlie.png', class: "img img-circle", height: 120, width: 120)  %>
          <br>
          <h4><b>Charlie Matlack, CEO</b></h4>
          <p> Charlie earned his Ph.D. in Electrical Engineering from the University of Washington.  He attended Harvery Mudd College as an undergraduate, which provided a background in multiple engineering disciplines with an emphasis on systems design. He is an expert in electrical and mechanical design and prototyping, in particular with embedded digital systems. His dissertation work was on novel interfaces for enabling individuals to control prosthetics and computers using individual neurons in the brain. He has a strong interest in entrepreneurship, and has participated in the UW Business Plan Competition twice. The second time led to the formation of PotaVida, Inc. Looking forward, Charlie hopes to gain a better understanding of how to leverage for-profit business and technology development models to provide market-based solutions to the developing world.
        </div><!-- col-lg-3 -->
        
        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <%= image_tag('jackie.png', class: "img img-circle", height: 120, width: 120)  %>
          <br>
          <h4><b>Jackie Linnes</b></h4>
          <p>Jackie holds a Ph.D. in Bioengineering and a certificate in Global Health from the University of Washington.  She is an expert in bacterial pathogens and implementing engineering solutions that improve global health.  Jackie has extensive global health implementation experience, including the development of the SODIS indicator as well as leading an assessment of user response and usage of improved cooking stoves for Engineers Without Borders in rural Bolivia.  Jackie has developed initial prototypes and evaluated stove efficiency and chimney design to further improve stoves.
        </div><!-- col-lg-3 -->
        
        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <%= image_tag('tyler.png', class: "img img-circle", height: 120, width: 120)  %>
          <br>
          <h4><b>Tyler Davis</b></h4>
          <p>Tyler is a Ph.D. student at the Evans School of Public Policy.  He has a background in benefit cost analysis, and field work in less developed countries.  His dissertation work is on environmental policy in less developed countries, specifically marine natural resource policy.  His research includes economic modeling in Indonesia (two years), development of principles and standards for benefit cost analysis for social programs (three years), and benefit cost analysis of social services (two years).  Tyler has extensive experience conducting fieldwork in less developed countries, including Indonesia (two years) and Mexico (one year). Tyler is currently a Ph.D. student in public policy and a research team leader on benefit cost analysis of access to information and communication technology in Chile.
        </div><!-- col-lg-3 -->
        
